<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Martha Kalifatidis and Michael Brunelli are one of the few success stories to come out of Channel Nine's disastrous Married At First Sight.</p>

<p>But it hasn't always been smooth sailing for the reality TV power couple, who secretly split for a few hours recently before getting back together.</p>

<p>During an appearance on The Kyle and Jackie O Show on Thursday, Martha was asked by host Kyle Sandilands if she and Michael had ever broken up before.</p>

<p>Heartbreaking: Former Married At First Sight stars Martha Kalifatidis and Michael Brunelli</p>

<p>'For like a few hours,' the 31-year-old admitted, before admitting that they didn't even spend any time apart during the split because they were still stuck in the same house together.</p>

<p>Earlier this year, the former Married At First Sight stars shared a number of text messages to their Instagram accounts which appeared to indicate they had split. </p>

<p>However, it was later revealed to be a publicity stunt to promote her new internet service provider.</p>

<p>Spilling the tea! During an appearance on The Kyle and Jackie O Show on Thursday, Martha was asked by host Kyle Sandilands if she and Michael had ever broken up before</p>

<p>'Me and Michael have not broken up,' Martha said on Instagram at the time.</p>

<p>'We are actually really happy together. But we have broken up with our telco provider!' </p>

<p>Martha then launched into a lengthy spiel spruiking Circles Life Australia and their data plan.</p>

<p>'For like a few hours,' the 31-year-old admitted, before admitting that they didn't even spend any time apart during the split because they were still stuck in the same house together</p>

<p>Rather than being angry over the con, the majority of the pair's fans appeared very relieved they had not split, with numerous comments praising the prank. </p>

<p>Earlier this year, the couple moved in together in Sydney's trendy Bondi.</p>

<p>Michael currently runs his own online fitness program, while Martha is one of Sydney's most successful Instagram influencers.</p>

<p>Love story: Martha and Michael are one of the few success stories to come out of Channel Nine's disastrous Married At First Sight</p>
